There was a wholesome moment during Norwich’s Premier League clash against Brentford on Saturday. Norwich defender Brandon Williams was left angry after being fouled and appeared ready to confront his opponent. However, after realising that it was Christian Eriksen who brought him down, Williams proceeded to hug the Denmark international. Newcastle Battle Tottenham In Race To Zaniolo Mane Edges Liverpool Closer To Man City Both players were seen smiling following the incident. Eriksen was making his first competitive start since he suffered a cardiac arrest while playing for Denmark against Finland at Euro 2020 in June last year. It was Eriksen’s second appearance for Brentford after he made his debut as a substitute in a defeat to Newcastle. Against Norwich Eriksen completed the full 90 minutes as Brentford managed to secure a 3-1 victory. Ivan Toney scored a hat-trick for Brentford, which included two penalties. POLL Although Teemu Pukki got a goal back for Norwich late on, it was Brentford who took all three points to end their eight game winless run in the Premier League.